Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
read_design_stack_config(25.10)                read_design_stack_config(25.10)

Name
       read_design_stack_config

Syntax
       read_design_stack_config

       [-help]

       [-avoid_floorplan_change]

       [-chipName <NameOfChip>]

       [-manufacturing_grid <grid>]

       [-power_config_file <PowerConnectionFile>]

       [-topNetlist <VerilogFileName>]

       [-xml <StackedDieFileName>]

       Loads  the  die  stacking config file (*.xml) for Innovus to understand
       the 3D-IC top-level structure.

       You can use this command before or after the init_design command.  When
       you  use  read_design_stack_config  before  init_design, in addition to
       loading the die stacking information into the memory, it patches up the
       virtual techLEF of the 3DIC top cell and the  Verilog  netlist  if  the
       init_lef_file  and  init_verilog  variables are not set before init_de-
       sign. If you use read_design_stack_config after init_design,  when  the
       top  design  (Netlist,  tech LEF) has already been loaded into Innovus,
       but without XML. Without the XML, Innovus does not know  that  the  top
       cell is the top of a 3DIC design. Therefore, XML is required to let In-
       novus  know  the  vertical position and face up/down information of the
       dies for the GUI display and the contact layer mapping relationship.

       When the top-level netlist  is  missing,  read_design_stack_config  can
       help  generate a virtual netlist, but the pins are floating so that you
       can still load the 3D-IC design into Innovus with iHDB. Only top is  in
       the  virtual netlist. read_design_stack_config internally calls addInst
       to add other dies.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each read_design_stack_config parameter. For a
              detailed description of the command and all of  its  parameters,
              use the man command:

              man read_design_stack_config

       -avoid_floorplan_change
              When  you  specify  this option, the floorplan and die instances
              will not be created.

       -chipName <NameOfChip>
              Specifies the name to be used when the current die is  instanti-
              ated.

       -manufacturing_grid <grid>
              Specifies  the manufacturing grid. However, if the manufacturing
              grid is set by TLEF, read_design_stack_config  does  not  update
              the manufacturing grid and prints an error.

       -power_config_file <PowerConnectionFile>
              Specifies the file name of the power connection.

       -topNetlist <VerilogFileName>
              Specifies the file name of the top-level netlist verilog.

       -xml <StackedDieFileName>
              Specifies the file name of the stacked die.

